body:
I thought perhaps inheritance wasn't supported, but looking at the source code, it looks like it should be.  This seems like a very straight forward example so maybe I'm just missing something or made some stupid mistake.  If so, sorry in advance.

I passed the 2012 flag.  I'm using the v10 branch updated 3-4 days ago.
It core dumps after an ivl assertion while scoping the derived class.  The error message is:

> /code/Hardware/verif/object/object.sv:27: assert: elab_scope.cc:503: failed assertion scope
> Aborted (core dumped)

Line 27 is:
`class test extends object;`

Class declarations:

```
class object;
  string Type;

  function new(string iName="object");
  begin
    Type = "object";
  end 
  endfunction
endclass

class test extends object;

  function new(string iName="test");
  begin
    super.new(iName);
    Type = {Type, ".test"};
  end 
  endfunction
endclass
```

Stimulus code:

```
module top();

  object obj;
  test tst;

  initial begin
    obj = new("obj");
    $display("obj type is '%s'", obj.Type);
    tst = new("tst");
    $display("tst type is '%s'", tst.Type);
  end 
endmodule
```

Oh, and I tried changing 'object' to something else as well in case there was some conflict, but the results were the same.

